file.title: AMM PART II-1285 - CHAPTER 20-30-01-02 - FUEL AND SERVICE FLUIDS - MAINTENANCE PRACTICES

page.data: AIRCRAFT MAINTENANCE MANUAL FUEL AND SERVICE FLUIDS - MAINTENANCE PRACTICES EFFECTIVITY: ALL 1. General A. This subchapter gives a list of the products approved to be used on, and for the servicing of, the aircraft, with their most usual suppliers. B. The correct procedure to use the products, and for filling, charging, or other applications is given in the chapters referred to below. C. Fuels with the same specification MIL-, FED. SPEC., but of different makes, can be mixed. D. Products listed on the QPL (Qualified Products List) for MIL specifications, referred to in this subchapter, are automatically approved to be used on the aircraft. E. Possible alternative products are listed opposite to the same group of chapters where the indicated product(s) is(are) referenced to. F. All Phosphate Ester-Base Hydraulic Fluid Type IV are miscible and compatible and may be used with each other in any and all proportions. G. The supplier/manufacturer addresses are listed in the section AMM MPP 20-30-00/200. EMB-145 - AMM 1285 General 20-30-01 Page 1 of 3 Rev 54 - Apr 27/18 Copyright ÃÂ© by Embraer S.A.
